{"parentUuid":"35ea6613-77ff-44cd-921d-d9f154b359bb","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab5204ea630c41b6e","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsYNBuBPQdSTdCFZkxPd","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_0183Tjnjr6qe7DhNoNwYFgmu","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\.pipeline\\surface-delta.md","content":"# Attack-surface delta — quota administration (GET/DELETE /v1/quotas)\n\nBest-effort hint for the security stage; reconciled against the actual diff, not authoritative.\n\n## New entry points\n\n- `GET /v1/quotas` — `src/api/routes/quotas.py:59` (`list_quotas_endpoint`). Admin-scoped read of\n  the caller's own tenant's full quota list. No request body/query/path parameter.\n- `DELETE /v1/quotas` — `src/api/routes/quotas.py:68` (`delete_quota_endpoint`). Admin-scoped\n  removal of one `(customer_id, metric)` cap, identified by query parameters\n  (`customer_id`, `metric`). 204 on success, 404 if absent.\n\nBoth reuse the existing `_require_admin_and_throttled` dependency (`src/api/routes/quotas.py:26`)\nverbatim — no new auth path, scope, or dependency chain.\n\n## New trust boundaries\n\nNone. No outbound third-party call, no new subprocess/exec, no new SSRF-capable fetch. Both new\nroutes only read/write the existing `quotas` table over the existing `app <-> RDS` boundary\nalready used by `PUT /v1/quotas`.\n\n## New data flows / sinks\n\n- `SELECT customer_id, metric, limit_per_window FROM quotas WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id ORDER BY\n  customer_id, metric` — `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py::list_quotas` (parameterized `text()`,\n  no string interpolation).\n- `DELETE FROM quotas WHERE api_key_id = :api_key_id AND customer_id = :customer_id AND metric =\n  :metric RETURNING customer_id` — `src/repositories/quotas_repo.py::delete_quota` (parameterized\n  `text()`).\n- No new table, no new stored field. Both queries operate on the pre-existing `quotas` table\n  (migration `0003`), which already carries the `quotas_tenant_isolation` FORCE RLS policy.\n- **Stored-field classification (unchanged, no new field):** `customer_id` / `metric` /\n  `limit_per_window` were already classified **non-sensitive operational config** at rest under\n  RDS SSE (storage-level) in the metric-quotas plan. This feature stores no new field — it only\n  reads (GET) and removes (DELETE) existing rows — so no field-level KDF/KMS applies here; the\n  `data_protection_waiver` in `.pipeline/acceptance.md` frontmatter documents this explicitly for\n  the reconciliation.\n- New log event: `quota.delete` (INFO) — `src/services/quota_service.py::delete_tenant_quota`,\n  emitted via the existing structlog facade (`src/logging`), which auto-redacts `customer_id`.\n\n## New privilege / authz surface\n\n- Both new routes are authenticated + admin-scope-gated (`scope == 'admin'`), identical to the\n  existing `PUT /v1/quotas`. No new scope value, no privilege widening beyond what `PUT` already\n  grants an admin key.\n- DELETE is a net-new **destructive** capability (removing a cap re-enables unlimited usage for\n  that `(customer_id, metric)` until a new `PUT`) — mitigated by the same admin-scope gate + tenant\n  isolation (`api_key_id` filter + FORCE RLS) already covering `PUT`/GET. This is the STRIDE\n  Elevation-of-Privilege / IDOR-BOLA row the plan calls out (AC8 proves cross-tenant DELETE is\n  invisible, matching zero rows -> 404).\n\n## Other changes\n\n- `src/api/middleware.py` — added `\"DELETE\"` to `CORSMiddleware.allow_methods`. No live-control\n  effect (empty origin allowlist, server-to-server API); completeness only, matching the plan.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":622,"cache_read_input_tokens":128267,"output_tokens":1645,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":622},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1645,"cache_read_input_tokens":128267,"cache_creation_input_tokens":622,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":622,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsYNAPedDCA5QaxbppPB","attributionAgent":"implementation","type":"assistant","uuid":"dab581bf-5102-49de-a71f-0dabc4eba14d","timestamp":"2026-07-10T01:53:19.906Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"claude-vscode","cwd":"C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test","sessionId":"cb1e5971-0f87-4706-9a1d-09f830df9e6f","version":"2.1.205","gitBranch":"feature/quota-admin"}
