{"parentUuid":"f87b9cd5-3ac0-4b84-8c22-3c7d05373935","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"ab5204ea630c41b6e","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-5","id":"msg_011CcsYQUNBie65bU8bdHTEo","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Implementation is complete. Summary of what changed:\n\n## Files modified\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\schemas\\quotas.py` — added `QuotaDeleteParams` (reuses module-level `CustomerId`/`Metric` allowlists, `extra='forbid'`).\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\repositories\\quotas_repo.py` — added `QuotaListItem` dataclass, `list_quotas()` (ordered, `api_key_id`-scoped `SELECT`), `delete_quota()` (parameterized `DELETE … RETURNING`, returns bool).\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\services\\quota_service.py` — added `list_tenant_quotas()` (no business log, mirrors `GET /v1/usage`) and `delete_tenant_quota()` (raises `HTTPException(404)` on no match; emits `quota.delete` INFO on success).\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\routes\\quotas.py` — added `GET /v1/quotas` and `DELETE /v1/quotas` handlers, both on the existing `_require_admin_and_throttled` dependency.\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\src\\api\\middleware.py` — added `\"DELETE\"` to CORS `allow_methods`.\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\test_schemas_quotas.py` — added `QuotaDeleteParams` unit tests (accept, missing-field, mass-assignment, injection/oversized, hypothesis property test).\n\n## File created\n- `C:\\Users\\brett\\OneDrive\\Documents\\GitHub\\meterly-pipeline-test\\tests\\integration\\test_quotas_list_delete.py` — 18 integration tests covering AC1–AC17 and AC19 (AC18 delegated to security; AC14 verified negatively — no new Alembic migration file).\n\n## No migration\nPer the plan, no schema change — GET/DELETE operate on the existing `quotas` table (revision `0003`).\n\n## Test-first record\nRecorded per-unit in `.pipeline/implementation-progress.md`: schema tests written red (ImportError) → `QuotaDeleteParams` implemented → green (31 passed); then the full integration test file written red (17 failures / route+attribute errors) → repo/service/route/CORS implemented → green (18 passed).\n\n## Full suite status\n211 passed (excluding `tests/integration/test_perf_k6_load.py`, which has one pre-existing, machine-load-dependent perf test unrelated to this diff — it passed in isolation, confirming it's not a regression from this change). Coverage: 88% overall (≥85% gate met); all new modules report 100%.\n\n## Self-checks\n- Diff vs. plan: all 7 planned files present in the change set (`PROJECT.md` was already modified before this session, unrelated).\n- Secrets/RLS/input-validation scan: clean — both new queries filter by `api_key_id`, DELETE query params route through `QuotaDeleteParams`'s anchored allowlist.\n- `.pipeline/surface-delta.md` written describing the two new entry points, no new trust boundaries, the new `quotas` read/delete data flows (with the `data_protection_waiver` note — no new stored field), and the new destructive DELETE privilege surface."}],"stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1293,"cache_read_input_tokens":130611,"output_tokens":1254,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1293},"inference_geo":"not_available","iterations":[{"input_tokens":2,"output_tokens":1254,"cache_read_input_tokens":130611,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1293,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1293,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"type":"message"}],"speed":"standard"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcsYQTA1nReJVMX5ubrTY",